## Why this is better

It removes the fragile date parsing completely and matches your actual filenames better.

Your recent errors were all caused by the tasklet skipping before retry because the date extractor kept returning empty. The screenshots clearly showed that exact skip path. 

## One note on cleanup behavior

With this version, cleanup deletes files that share the same base name only, not everything from the same date. That is usually safer too. It also fits your retry flow better than date matching when names look like `finance_invoices_202401011030.zip.pgp`.

